TY  - JOUR
AU  - Allen, Beth
AU  - Hellwig, Martin
T1  - Bertrand-Edgeworth Oligopoly in Large Markets
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297646
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 53
IS  - 2
SP  - 175
EP  - 204
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The relation between perfectly competitive and monopolistically competitive equilibria is analysed for a Bertrand-Edgeworth model of a single market in which capacity constrained firms choose prices as strategies. The market always has a Nash equilibrium in pure or mixed strategies. As the number of firms increases, the corresponding equilibria converge in distribution to a perfectly competitive price. This result provides a justification for perfect competition that is based on an explicit account of price formation. However, monopoly prices persist with a positive but vanishing probability. Regularity or well defined inverse demand functions are not required.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297646
ER  - 



